# Migration from Firebase to Supabase & FastAPI Backend Walkthrough

We have successfully migrated the frontend authentication provider from Firebase to Supabase, and redirected all user e-commerce data operations (Carts, Orders, and Addresses) to call the local FastAPI backend server (`http://localhost:8000`) instead of direct Firebase Firestore reads/writes.

---

## Key Changes Made

### 1. Authentication Integration
* **Root Session Sync ([App.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/App.jsx))**: Added a root `useEffect` listener to listen to Supabase `onAuthStateChange` events. It captures user profiles and JWT access tokens, automatically dispatching them to the Redux store to maintain a reactive authenticated session.
* **Email & Google Login ([SignIn.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/logIn/SignIn.jsx))**: Replaced Firebase's email/password sign-in and Google Popup login with `supabase.auth.signInWithPassword` and `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth`. Removed legacy firestore calls.
* **Account Registration ([CreateAccount.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/logIn/CreateAccount.jsx))**: Replaced Firebase `createUserWithEmailAndPassword` with `supabase.auth.signUp`. User full names are sent under Supabase user metadata fields.
* **Sign Out Handling ([header.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/header/header.jsx) & [QuickCommerceHeader.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/header/QuickCommerceHeader.jsx))**: Cleaned out `signOut(auth)` imports from Firebase and switched to calling `supabase.auth.signOut()`.

