* **Checkout Order Placement ([OrderSummary.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/checkout/OrderSummary.jsx))**: Swapped Firestore order creation with `POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/orders`. On success, it fetches updated orders from the backend to sync context state and navigates the user to `/orders`.
* **Orders Context ([userOrderContext.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/context/userOrderContext.jsx))**: Fetches orders from `GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/orders` and separates active and cancelled orders, syncing them directly to Redux.
