### 7. Troubleshooting and Resolution of CORS/401 & Database Connection Errors
* **CORS & 401 Unauthorized Fix ([SignIn.jsx](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/frontend/src/components/logIn/SignIn.jsx))**: Fixed the issue where manual sign-in dispatched user details to Redux without the `token` key, overriding the correct session token with `undefined` and causing all backend endpoints to return `401 Unauthorized`. The login handler was updated to retrieve and pass `data.session?.access_token` on sign-in.
* **Database Connection Fix ([backend/.env](file:///d:/Coding/HackOn/backend/.env))**: Resolved `socket.gaierror: [Errno 11001] getaddrinfo failed` and `WinError 1231: The network location cannot be reached`. Because the default database host `db.svdwcionemyzyptdzymj.supabase.co` is IPv6-only and local environments often lack IPv6 routing capability, we updated the connection URL to target the IPv4-compatible Supabase connection pooler host `aws-1-ap-southeast-1.pooler.supabase.com`. We configured it on port `5432` (Session Mode) to avoid prepared-statement conflicts with SQLAlchemy + asyncpg.

